                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/16543: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        President of the Chinese Executive Yuan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chiang Kai-shek</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-28">March 28,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I wish to express my appreciation of your telegram of March 18<note n="26"
                        xml:id="d653fn1">See Press Release No. 123 of March 22, <ref
                            target="#pg_613">p. 613</ref>.</note> which contains an inspiring
                    expression of the splendid morale and confidence of the Chinese people. Their
                    unimpaired spirit, notwithstanding their burdens and sacrifices, stimulates and
                    reinforces the confidence of free peoples everywhere that with resolute
                    determination and cooperation on the part of those who are committed to it the
                    cause of freedom and justice will unquestionably prevail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
